+{"actor":"mayor","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-02T12:10:50Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":2607,"issue_id":"bd-qwa3","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"beads/polecats/obsidian\",\"status\":\"hooked\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"bd-qwa3\",\"title\":\"bd backup exports entire wisps table into issues.jsonl — massive pollution\",\"description\":\"bd backup in backup_export.go (lines 153-170) blindly appends the entire wisps table into issues.jsonl. This means:\\n\\n- HQ backup: 16,645 rows, but only 1,385 are real issues. 15,270 are wisps (13,279 open).\\n- Beads backup: 2,093 rows, 1,817 are wisps.\\n- Restoring from backup would re-create all wisp pollution.\\n- Same pattern for events.jsonl (wisp_events), comments.jsonl (wisp_comments), dependencies.jsonl (wisp_dependencies), labels.jsonl (wisp_labels).\\n\\nThe daemon's JSONL git backup (jsonl_git_backup.go) already handles this correctly with scrubWhereClause filtering. bd backup never got the same treatment.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\nIn backup_export.go, skip wisps from the export entirely. They are ephemeral by definition (PRIMING.md Root-Only Wisps principle). If the database needs disaster recovery, wisps can be regenerated — they represent patrol step tracking, not durable work product.\\n\\nSpecifically:\\n1. Remove the `if hasWisps { exportTableAppend(...wisps...) }` block (lines 163-169)\\n2. Remove the UNION ALL with wisp_events, wisp_comments, wisp_dependencies, wisp_labels (lines 172-225)\\n3. Or, if audit preservation is desired, filter to only include closed wisps with a WHERE clause\\n\\n## Key file\\n- cmd/bd/backup_export.go — the entire export function\\n\\n## Context\\nThe daemon backup at gastown/internal/daemon/jsonl_git_backup.go already does this right (line 54: AND id NOT LIKE '%-wisp-%', line 209-218: supplementalTables excludes wisp tables). This is the same pattern, just needs to be applied to bd backup.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"steve.yegge@gmail.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T20:10:40Z\",\"created_by\":\"mayor\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T20:10:40Z\"}"}
